availablePart.name: CPU
availablePart.description: In computing, a processor or processing unit is an electronic circuit which performs operations on some external data source, usually memory or some other data stream.

availablePart.name: RAM
availablePart.description: Random-access memory is a form of computer data storage that stores data and machine code currently being used. A random-access memory device allows data items to be read or written in almost the same amount of time irrespective of the physical location of data inside the memory.
